14/04/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- One of the founders of the ruling Justice and Development Party (AKP), Abdullatif Sener, will announce the formation of a new political party by the end of April, media reported on Monday (April 13th). 
Sener, who served as economy minister and deputy prime minister between 2002 and 2007, quit the ruling party ahead of the 2007 parliamentary elections. 
He is expected to announce his new party on April 26th and to present its founding members, including about 40 former members of parliament and ministers, to the public. 
The new party plans to participate in the 2011 general elections. 
(Radikal, Yeni Safak -13/04/09)
